  <div class="block-3">
    <div class="inner-block">
      <section class="biography" id="biography">
        <h1 class="label">Biography</h1>
        <div class="govspeak">
<p>Jim began his career in the Inland Revenue as an Inspector of Taxes in 1984. In January 2009, he was appointed Director of Corporation Tax and VAT, responsible for optimising the design and delivery of these business taxes. Jim became Director of Personal Tax Customer Operations in March 2011, and Director Personal Tax Operations in October 2011. He was appointed Director General Business Tax on 16 April 2012. Most recently, Jim was appointed as HMRC’s Second Permanent Secretary and Deputy Chief Executive, taking up the post on 1 January 2018. Alongside these roles, he is continuing as Tax Assurance Commissioner.</p>
</div>
      </section>

      <div class="current-roles" id="current-roles">
          <section class="role_appointment role" id="role_appointment_3710">
            <h1 id="tax-assurance-commissioner">Tax Assurance Commissioner</h1>
            <div class="govspeak">
<p><abbr title="HM Revenue and Customs">HMRC</abbr>’s Tax Assurance Commissioner is the Head of Profession for Tax, and oversees and provides assurance of large tax settlements.</p>

<p>The Commissioner oversees the assurance and dispute governance arrangements that allow Parliament and the public to be confident that <abbr title="HM Revenue and Customs">HMRC</abbr> secures the right tax under the law when resolving tax disputes.</p>

<p>The Commissioner does not directly engage with taxpayers to discuss their specific tax liabilities, nor is he responsible for the <abbr title="HM Revenue and Customs">HMRC</abbr> operational units that manage taxpayers’ compliance.</p>

</div>
            <div class="read-more">
                <p class="js-hide-other-departments organisations-name-list">
  <a class="organisation-link" href="/government/organisations/hm-revenue-customs">HM Revenue & Customs</a>
</p>

            </div>
</section>          <section class="role_appointment role" id="role_appointment_4502">
            <h1 id="deputy-chief-executive-and-second-permanent-secretary">Deputy Chief Executive and Second Permanent Secretary</h1>
            <div class="govspeak">
<p>The Deputy Chief Executive and Second Permanent Secretary is HMRC’s lead for exiting the EU, the policy partnership with HM Treasury and HMRC’s tax profession.</p>
</div>
            <div class="read-more">
                <p class="js-hide-other-departments organisations-name-list">
